<subSubSection id="B6896573FFD9FF87FFDFFB89FCCD7829" pageId="17" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FE2C36F8FFD9FF87FFDFFB89FF357943" blockId="17.[107,222,1108,1126]" box="[107,222,1108,1126]" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="CCE7EAEAFFD9FF87FFDFFB89FF357943" bold="true" box="[107,222,1108,1126]" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">Comments</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FE2C36F8FFD9FF87FFDEFBA7FCCD7829" blockId="17.[106,1097,1146,1292]" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">
Within the 
<taxonomicName id="39934D7BFFD9FF87FF53FBA7FE2579B4" authorityName="KERTESZ ER" authorityYear="1903" box="[231,462,1146,1169]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Heteromeringia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="czernyi">
<emphasis id="CCE7EAEAFFD9FF87FF53FBA7FE2579B4" box="[231,462,1146,1169]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">Heteromeringia czernyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, 
<taxonomicName id="39934D7BFFD9FF87FD96FBA7FD4079B7" authorityName="Lonsdale &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2007" box="[546,683,1146,1170]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Heteromeringia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aphotisma">
<emphasis id="CCE7EAEAFFD9FF87FD96FBA7FD4079B7" box="[546,683,1146,1170]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">H. aphotisma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, like 
<taxonomicName id="39934D7BFFD9FF87FD53FBA7FCBB79B4" authorityName="K ERTESZ" authorityYear="1903" box="[743,848,1146,1169]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Heteromeringia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="czernyiczernyi">
<emphasis id="CCE7EAEAFFD9FF87FD53FBA7FCBB79B4" box="[743,848,1146,1169]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">H. czernyiczernyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="39934D7BFFD9FF87FC3CFBA7FC1879B7" baseAuthorityName="WILLISTON ILLIST" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[904,1011,1146,1170]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Heteromeringia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipes">
<emphasis id="CCE7EAEAFFD9FF87FC3CFBA7FC1879B7" box="[904,1011,1146,1170]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">H. flavipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has retained dark colouration and an upcurved bristle in the posterodorsal corner of the anepisternum. Unlike these two dark species, however, 
<taxonomicName id="39934D7BFFD9FF87FDB8FB65FD7F79EA" authorityName="Lonsdale &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2007" box="[524,660,1207,1231]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Heteromeringia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aphotisma">
<emphasis id="CCE7EAEAFFD9FF87FDB8FB65FD7F79EA" box="[524,660,1207,1231]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">H. aphotisma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also has an additional reclinate fronto-orbital bristle (synapomorphic of the rest of the group), entirely dusky wings, brown legs (excluding the mid and hind tarsi) and a much darker head, easily separating it.
</paragraph>
